<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE topic
        SYSTEM "https://resources.jetbrains.com/writerside/1.0/xhtml-entities.dtd">
<topic xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
       xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="https://resources.jetbrains.com/writerside/1.0/topic.v2.xsd"
       title="What's New in Azd" id="Azd-Whats-New">

    <primary-label ref="azd"/>
    <secondary-label ref="azd_version"/>

    <p>Discover the latest features and improvements in the AZD plugin V2026.1.45.</p>

    <chapter title="Enhanced AI Capabilities" id="enhanced-ai">
        <p>This release brings significant updates to our AI-powered features, including support for the latest models and local providers.</p>
        <img src="ai_configuration_settings.png" alt="AI Configuration Settings" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
        <list>
            <li><p><b>Support for Latest Models:</b> Now supporting GPT-4o and the latest Claude 3.5 models.</p></li>
            <li><p><b>Analyze Issues:</b> A new toggle in settings allows the AI to automatically analyze linked work items to provide better context for PR descriptions.</p></li>
            <li><p><b>MCP Support:</b> Experimental support for Model Context Protocol (MCP) to allow AI models to interact with external tools.</p></li>
        </list>
        <img src="ai_setting_provider.png" alt="AI Provider Settings" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Pipeline Approvals and Validations" id="pipeline-approvals">
        <p>Manage pipeline gatekeepers directly from the IDE. You can now view and respond to pending environment approvals and manual validation tasks.</p>
        <img src="approva_bottom.png" alt="Pipeline Approvals" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
        <p>When a pipeline run is blocked, the approvals appear in the build header and the stages list, allowing you to approve or reject with a comment.</p>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Advanced Pipeline Test Insights" id="pipeline-tests">
        <p>The Pipeline test result panel has been overhauled with new features to improve traceability and analysis:</p>
        <img src="pipeline_test_results_v2.png" alt="Pipeline Test Results" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
        <list>
            <li><p><b>Sorting and Filtering:</b> Quickly find failed or long-running tests with the new toolbar controls.</p></li>
            <li><p><b>Test Summary:</b> A new header provides a real-time summary of test execution (passed, failed, skipped, and pass percentage).</p></li>
            <li><p><b>Traceability:</b> Seamlessly link automated tests to Azure DevOps test cases.</p></li>
        </list>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="AI-Powered Log Analysis" id="log-analysis">
        <p>Get help diagnosing pipeline failures without leaving the IDE. The new AI chat integration for logs analyzes failed stages and suggests fixes.</p>
        <img src="pipeline_logs_ai_chat.png" alt="AI Chat for Logs" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="PR Metrics Dashboard" id="azd_pr_metrics">
        <p>A new comprehensive dashboard to track your team's Pull Request metrics and performance.</p>
        <img src="pr_metrics_dashboard.png" alt="PR Metrics Dashboard" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Improved Navigation and UI" id="ui-improvements">
        <list>
            <li><p><b>Timeline Commit Links:</b> Clicking on commit SHAs in the PR timeline now opens the PR details view in the IDE instead of the browser.</p></li>
            <li><p><b>Sort Controls:</b> PR and Pipeline lists now feature a dedicated sort button for easier organization.</p></li>
        </list>
        <img src="sort_pipeline_and_pr_inline_button.png" alt="New Sort Button" style="block" thumbnail="true"/>
    </chapter>

</topic>
